e erlaubt Aufschlüsse über die Aufteilung und Funktion der einzelnen Räume. Zehn Meister zu dieser Zeit ermöglichen Aussagen über ihre Tätigkeit als Bader und Wundärzte.  aThis book examines the 100-year history (1480–1580) of Bath culture in Rattenberg, offering an overview of thermal baths, mineral baths, and natural spas, including the public baths of the early modern era. The bathhouse buildings that survive to this day offer insights into the division and function of the individual rooms. Ten contemporaries provide information about their work as barber-surgeons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aKörperpflege, Rattenberg in Tirol, Regeneration, Wundarzt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2016z9783110485189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7767/978320579297040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783205792970423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783205792970.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016